{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/first-principles","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building 🌩️ cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.​\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ​Conference & Community builder. Camper. 🏕️ 🚐","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"b24b6d01-0091-5011-9bd5-e8771ee85549","name":"first-principles","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/first-principles.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"A question I brought to "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"SoCraTes 2018"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://coderbyheart.com/socrates-2018","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nwas one that formed in the recent months when I was onboarding a new developer\nto a greenfield project. The project they going to work on is developed as a\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"walking skeleton"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://codeclimate.com/blog/kickstart-your-next-project-with-a-walking-skeleton/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":".\nAlthough the architecture is complete, there is not enough flesh on it to\nclearly see the "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"patterns"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" I have used when designing it. Right now every\ncomponent looks like a unicorn and it is hard to see the underlying principles\nthat went into the design—simply because there is not enough code to provide\ngood heuristics."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I was looking for a way to provide a resource "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"outside of the code"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" which\ndocuments the gut feelings that lead to this architecture. These gut feelings\nare a result of reading books, articles and building many different software\nprojects, so there is not "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"one school"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" of thought, but a amalgamation of\nhundreds of resources and experiences that form the principles that influence my\ndecisions."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"But what "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"are"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" First Principles?"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/1QcpdY9786COUQ7xz28k0w/ccbcccd1a6c4f1683d72b91a822ef15e/IMG_20180824_114145297.jpg?w=3006&h=4120","alt":"IMG 20180824 114145297"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["notresponsive"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"In this session I listed mine and we collected some more:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Push to deploy"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"S.O.L.I.D."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"No global state"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"No monolith"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Version dependencies"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Simplicity"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Done > Perfect"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Show > Tell"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Code Stewardship"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"While some of those are fairly easy to explain (like S.O.L.I.D. where extensive\ndocumentation "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"can easily be found"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SOLID","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"),\nothers are horribly ambiguous, like "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Simplicity"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"In the course of the session we then collected, how principles are shared within\nteams. One recurring characteristic was that they are usually very project\nspecific and are best understood if they are explained using real examples from\nthe project's source code."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"A good method to share these principles is pairing when concrete situations\narise."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Multiple participants shared that they had good experiences using an internal\nStackoverflow (or a home-grown solution similar to that), where developers would\nbring up principles they discover or certain implementation details they did not\nfully understand so it could be discussed what the underlying principle was, and\nwhether it still applies. This forum-style aproach can also serves as a good way\nto document technical dept, and the decisions that lead to keeping it in the\nsystem. It provides an easy way to regularly revisit these decisions after a\ncertain amount of time has passed and decide again whether to keep it or get rid\nof it."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/1pDFWFUVlefRoxVcO99vZz/0dd9a762925ff8faffc230e7fd15b734/IMG_20180824_114154631.jpg?w=3006&h=3742","a